article.headline: McHenry's 18 lead Western Kentucky over Liberty 70-68 in CUSA opener

images.name: Dontaie Allen's acrobatic finish extends the Hilltopper's lead
images.caption: Dontaie Allen drives to the rack and elevates for an acrobatic and-1 finish vs. the Flames.

article.linkText: McHenry's 18 lead Western Kentucky over Liberty 70-68 in CUSA opener
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- — Don McHenry's 18 points helped Western Kentucky defeat Liberty 70-68 to open Conference USA play on Saturday night. McHenry was 8 of 13 shooting (1 for 3 from 3-point range) for the Hilltoppers (12-3). Dontaie Allen was 4 of 6 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 5 from the line to add 13 points. Rodney Howard and Brandon Newman both added 11 points. The Hilltoppers extended their winning streak to eight games. The Flames (11-5) were led by Zach Cleveland, who posted 23 points, seven rebounds and two steals. Liberty also got 15 points, eight rebounds, four assists and four steals from Kyle Rode. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
